  "summary": {
    "macroSummary": "Markets are caught between geopolitical de-escalation hopes (US-Iran talks) driving risk-on sentiment and underlying structural concerns as oil volatility persists and crypto shows mixed accumulation signals. The bear market relief rally continues as equities rally late-session on conflict resolution bets, while bonds rise and the dollar weakens for the 6th straight session, suggesting risk appetite is cautiously improving.",
    "regimeImpact": "No regime change - this remains consistent with an oversold relief rally as geopolitical risk premium unwinds temporarily, but oil above $100 stagflation threshold and April 2 tariff deadline still loom as key structural concerns.",
    "actionItems": [
      "Monitor BMNR levels closely as Bitcoin reclaims $74K with strong ETF inflows but faces miner selling pressure - consider rolling up cash-secured puts if BTC holds above $62,300 structural level",
      "Maintain Maturity sector overweight as late-session equity rally appears driven by geopolitical relief rather than fundamental improvement",
      "Watch oil closely - if crude sustains above $100 despite talk optimism, stagflation risk increases and could end relief rally"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "Bitcoin above $74K with heavy institutional accumulation and ETF inflows crossing $500B suggests crypto strength may be sustainable.",
      "DXY falling for 6th straight session while bonds rise indicates risk-on rotation but with defensive undertones.",
      "Oil pulling back from highs on peace talk hopes, but staying elevated suggests supply risk premium remains embedded.",
      "Wall Street late-session rallies on conflict resolution bets show markets remain headline-driven and vulnerable to sentiment shifts."
    ]
